graph.name: 126_pubchem_gene_toc
pubchem_description: This classification was created automatically from the PubChem Gene TOC on 2023/01/31.
Note that in some cases a number of highly populated nodes - those for which all or nearly all IDs have information - have been left out of the tree.
The sections, along with their child subsections, that are not shown in this tree are: Create Date, Modify Date, and Record Title.

nodes.name: Biochemical Reactions
nodes.description: Biochemical reactions in which this gene or its gene products (e.g., the proteins encoded by the gene) is involved

nodes.name: Patents
nodes.description: Patent applications/documents that mention this gene.

nodes.name: Expression
nodes.description: Gene Expression Omnibus (GEO) is a public functional genomics data repository supporting MIAME-compliant data submissions.

nodes.name: Biomarker Information
nodes.description: The term "biomarker", a portmanteau of "biological marker", is a measurable substance in an organism whose presence is indicative of some phenomenon such as disease, infection, or environmental exposure.

nodes.name: BioAssays
nodes.description: Biological experiments deposited in PubChem BioAssay that were conducted against this gene or its gene products (e.g., proteins).

nodes.name: RNAi BioAssays
nodes.description: Functional genomic bioassays that tested RNAi reagents

nodes.name: Small-Molecule BioAssays
nodes.description: Bioassays that tested small molecules against this gene or its gene products (e.g., proteins).

nodes.name: Chemicals and Bioactivities
nodes.description: Drugs, chemical probes, curated ligands, and compounds tested against or related to this gene, along with associated bioactivity information.

nodes.name: Chemical Probes
nodes.description: Chemical probes developed by the Molecular Libraries Program (MLP) for this gene target, along with associated information.

nodes.name: Tested Compounds
nodes.description: Compounds tested against this gene in any bioassay deposited in PubChem.

nodes.name: Diseases and Phenotypes
nodes.description: Diseases and Phenotypes associated with this gene

nodes.name: Gene-Disease Associations
nodes.description: Diseases associated with this gene

nodes.name: GHR Health Conditions
nodes.description: Health conditions related to this gene, from Genetic Home Reference (GHR), which is now MedlinePlus Genetics.

nodes.name: KEGG Diseases
nodes.description: Diseases related to this gene, provided by the Kyoto Encyclopedia of Genes and Genomes (KEGG).

nodes.name: MedGen Diseases
nodes.description: Disease information from MedGen, NCBI's portal for conditions and phenotypes related to Medical Genetics.

nodes.name: OMIM Phenotypes
nodes.description: Phenotype information from the Online Mendelian Inheritance in Man (OMIM) database.

nodes.name: Gene Information
nodes.description: General information about this gene.

nodes.name: Taxonomy
nodes.description: Source organism of this gene.

nodes.name: Symbol
nodes.description: Official gene symbol provided by NCBI Gene, HGNC, or others

nodes.name: Interactions and Pathways
nodes.description: Interactions and pathways that involve this gene or its gene products (e.g., the proteins encoded by the gene)

nodes.name: Chemical-Gene Interactions
nodes.description: Interactions between chemicals and this gene or its gene products (e.g., the proteins encoded by the gene)

nodes.name: Interactions
nodes.description: Molecular interactions in which this gene or its gene products (e.g., the proteins encoded by the gene) is involved

nodes.name: Pathways
nodes.description: Biological pathways in which this gene or its gene products (e.g., the proteins encoded by the gene) is involved

nodes.name: Proteins
nodes.description: Proteins encoded by this gene.

nodes.name: Protein 3D Structures
nodes.description: Experimental three-dimensional (3D) structures of the protein encoded by this gene, determined through X-ray crystallography, NMR spectroscopy, etc.

nodes.name: AlphaFold Structures
nodes.description: Protein 3D structures, predicted by AlphaFold, an artificial intelligence (AI) system developed by DeepMind at Google. The image is generated by the iCn3D structure viewer developed at NCBI.

nodes.name: NCBI Protein Structures
nodes.description: Link to protein 3D structures from the NCBI Structure database, also known as the Molecular Modeling Database (MMDB).

nodes.name: PDB Structures
nodes.description: Protein 3D structures from the RCSB Protein Data Bank (PDB).

nodes.name: Protein Domains
nodes.description: A protein domain is a region of a protein that can adopt a particular 3-D structure and usually performs a function.  Many proteins contain multiple domains, each of which is responsible for a particular function or interaction, contributing to the overall role of a protein.

nodes.name: CDD Domains
nodes.description: Protein domain annotation from the NCBI Conserved Domain Database (CDD).

nodes.name: Pfam Domains
nodes.description: Protein domain annotation from the Pfam database.

nodes.name: Protein Function
nodes.description: Function(s) of the protein encoded by this gene.

nodes.name: Protein Isoforms
nodes.description: Protein isoforms are a set of highly similar proteins originating from a single gene or gene family.  While many perform the same or similar biological roles, some isoforms have unique functions.

nodes.name: Protein Targets
nodes.description: A list of proteins targeted in assays archived in PubChem and encoded by this gene.

nodes.name: Record Description
nodes.description: Textual summary about this PubChem record

nodes.name: Related Genes
nodes.description: Related gene records in PubChem (e.g., orthologous genes).

nodes.name: Orthologous Genes
nodes.description: Genes in other species that evolved from a common ancestral gene.

nodes.name: Classification
nodes.description: Classifications and ontologies of this gene.

nodes.name: Enzyme Classification
nodes.description: Enzyme classification of this enzyme (a protein or the encoding gene) from ENZYME, an enzyme nomenclature database at the SIB Swiss Institute of Bioinformatics.

nodes.name: NCI Thesaurus Tree
nodes.description: NCI Thesaurus (NCIt) hierarchy

nodes.name: MeSH Tree
nodes.description: The Medical Subject Headings (MeSH) tree for this entity.  MeSH is a controlled and hierarchically-organized vocabulary produced by the National Library of Medicine.

nodes.name: Gene Family
nodes.description: Gene family or group assigned to this gene (e.g., by  the Human Genome Organization (HUGO) Gene Nomenclature Committee (HGNC).  Groups may be either structural or functional.  A gene may belong to more than one group.

nodes.name: Gene Ontology: Biological Process
nodes.description: The Gene Ontology (GO) provides a structured, controlled terminology of 'terms' or 'classes' describing the functions of gene products, as well as the association of these terms with the gene products performing these functions.  The GO covers three domains: cellular component, molecular function, and biological process. This section provides the GO biological process terms for the gene.

nodes.name: Gene Ontology: Cellular Component
nodes.description: The Gene Ontology (GO) provides a structured, controlled terminology of 'terms' or 'classes' describing the functions of gene products, as well as the association of these terms with the gene products performing these functions.  The GO covers three domains: cellular component, molecular function, and biological process. This section provides the GO cellular component terms for the gene.

nodes.name: Gene Ontology: Molecular Function
nodes.description: The Gene Ontology (GO) provides a structured, controlled terminology of 'terms' or 'classes' describing the functions of gene products, as well as the association of these terms with the gene products performing these functions.  The GO covers three domains: cellular component, molecular function, and biological process. This section provides the GO molecular function terms for the gene.

nodes.name: ChEMBL Target Tree
nodes.description: Classification of this entity in the context of targets, provided by ChEMBL.

nodes.name: IUPHAR/BPS Guide to PHARMACOLOGY Target Classification
nodes.description: Classification of this entity in the context of targets, provided by the IUPHAR/BPS Guide to PHARMACOLOGY.

nodes.name: Literature
nodes.description: Scientific articles associated with this gene.  Some gene-literature associations in this section are provided by bioassay data contributors, while others are from curated resources, including DrugBank and IUPHAR/BPS Guide to PHARMACOLOGY.   This section also provides the lists of chemicals, genes/proteins, and diseases that are co-mentioned in scientific articles with this gene, as described in Zaslavsky et al., Front. Res. Metr. Anal., 2021, 6, 689059.

nodes.name: Gene-Gene Co-Occurrences in Literature
nodes.description: Gene-gene co-occurrences in literature highlight gene-gene pairs mentioned together in scientific articles. This may suggest an important relationship exists between the two. Note that a co-occurring gene entity is organism non-specific and could refer to a gene, protein, or enzyme. Also note that this content is not human curated. It is generated by text-mining algorithms that can be fooled such that a co-occurrence may be happenstance or a casual mention. The lists are ordered by relevancy as indicated by count of publications and other statistics, with the most relevant mentions appearing at the top.

nodes.name: Gene-Disease Co-Occurrences in Literature
nodes.description: Gene-disease co-occurrences in literature highlight gene-disease pairs mentioned together in scientific articles. This may suggest that an important relationship exists between the two. Please note that this content is not human curated. It is generated by text-mining algorithms that can be fooled such that a co-occurrence may be happenstance or a casual mention. The lists are ordered by relevancy as indicated by count of publications and other statistics, with the most relevant mentions appearing at the top.

nodes.name: DrugBank Interaction References

nodes.name: Guide to PHARMACOLOGY Interaction References
nodes.description: Citations about interaction with this gene, provided by the IUPHAR/BPS Guide to PHARMACOLOGY.

nodes.name: NLM Curated PubMed Citations
nodes.description: The NLM Curated PubMed Citations section links to all PubMed records that are tagged with the same MeSH term that has been associated with a particular gene.

The lists are ordered by relevancy as indicated by count of publications and other statistics, with the most relevant mentions appearing at the top.

nodes.name: GlyCosmos Gene
nodes.description: Gene identifier used in GlyCosmos, a web portal for accessing glycoscience data from various web resources.

nodes.name: Enzyme Commission (EC) Number
nodes.description: Enzyme Commission (EC) number for the enzyme encoded by this gene.  The EC number is a numerical classification scheme for enzymes, based on the chemical reactions they catalyze.  As a system of enzyme nomenclature, every EC number is associated with a recommended name for the corresponding enzyme-catalyzed reaction.
